  "doc_id": "60644",
  "text": "Decreased heartbeat perception accuracy is accompanied by significantly reduced HEP amplitudes in depressed individuals. [CITATION_1] The neurocircuitry underlying attention to visceral interoceptive sensations was assessed in unmedicated individuals with major depressive disorder (MDD) relative to controls. Activity in the dorsal mid-insula and a network of brain regions involved in emotion and visceral control were decreased in the MDD group. Moreover, resting state functional connectivity between the amygdala and the dorsal mid-insula cortex was increased in MDD and predictive of depression severity. [CITATION_2] Together, these results suggest that the brain representation of interoceptive focus may be altered in MDD.",
